Malamulele &#8211; A Limpopo woman and her son have been sentenced to a R24 000 fine for beating up her husband with a spade.Joyce Chauke, 46, and their son Ndhavuko Chauke, 22, of Xikundu village outside Malamulele, were released after paying the fine.Magistrate Daniel Maluleke sentenced them in the Malamulele Magistrate s Court on Monday. He said the two could have killed the man. If you have differences as husband and wife, you sit down and resolve it or call the elderly to help you. Or if you no longer want each other, you don&#8217;t turn to violence or kill each other, he said.Saselamani police spokesperson Warrant Officer Samuel Matsimbi said the two were arrested for assault with intent to do bodily harm.